cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for 3D registration of medical images, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of geodesic loss, which is a common optimization technique in ML, indicating that cs.AI is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on medical imaging, which suggests that cs.MED is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the registration of 3D images, which is a common topic in computer graphics (GR), making it a possible sub-category as well.
